  "prompt": "Is money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering is the process of making illegally obtained money (such as proceeds from criminal activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or terrorism) appear legitimate by disguising its true origin. This is typically done through a series of complex transactions or financial maneuvers.\n\nLaws against money laundering are in place to prevent criminals from profiting from their illegal activities and to maintain the integrity of financial systems. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including hefty fines, asset seizure, and lengthy prison sentences.\n\nIn addition to national laws, there are international efforts to combat money laundering, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), which sets global standards and promotes effective implementation of legal, regulatory, and operational measures to combat money laundering and terrorist financing.",
